-- Egyptian Stocks: Ezz Steel, Lecico and Misr Beni Suef Cement
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-05-08T13:04:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/egyptian-stocks-ezz-steel-and-lecico-egypt-are-active.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30)  advanced
0.6 percent to 5,056.09 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, the
highest level in more than a month.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Ezz Steel (ESRS)   increased as much as 1.7 percent to
7.37 Egyptian pounds before closing at 7.31 pounds, the highest
level in more than a week. Egypt’s biggest steel manufacturer
will pay shareholders as of today a 25-piaster dividend on May
13.  Lecico Egypt SAE (LCSW)   climbed 2.1 percent, the most in
more than two weeks, to 4.95 pounds. First-quarter profit for
the producer of sanitary ware and tiles rose 2 percent to 12.7
million pounds ($2.1 million). Revenue climbed 33 percent.  Misr Beni Suef Cement Co. (MBSC)   advanced 0.8 percent to
52.48 pounds, the highest level this month. Shareholders of the
Cairo-based producer of the building material approved a
dividend distribution of 5 Egyptian pounds a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
